This paper deals with the algorithmic complexity of counting problems, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science. The paper specifically focuses on Holant problems, which are a general framework for studying counting problems. This makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph homomorphisms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also introduces new polynomial time algorithms, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
